OL,6,FOn the 16th October 2024 at Llandudno
OL,7,FMagistrates Court, Dwr Cymru plead
OL,8,Fguilty to 15 out of the 18 charges. By
OL,9,Fthe 17th December 2024 the company
OL,10,Faccepted the remainder of the Taken
OL,11,Finto Consideration (TIC) charges.
OL,13,FUpon receiving its 2020 annual report,
OL,14,Fofficers for NRW say they were alarmed
OL,15,Fto find that the quality of the
OL,16,Finformation provided 'had noticeably
OL,17,Fdeteriorated compared to previous
OL,18,Fyears', with over 600 breaches
OL,19,Frecorded.
